-- Walgreen board approves $1 billion share buyback
-- 
-- Wed Oct 13, 2010 12:48pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/10/13/us-walgreen-idUSTRE69C4MY20101013

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - U.S. drugstore chain Walgreen Co ( WAG.N ) said its board has approved a buyback of $1 billion shares and set a regular quarterly dividend . 

 The retailer said the buyback program will expire at the end of 2012. The company said the latest dividend of 17.5 cents a share will be paid on December 11 to shareholders of record November 15. Walgreen shares were up 2.3 percent at $34.83 in midday trading on the New York Stock Exchange. (Reporting by Dhanya Skariachan. Editing by Robert MacMillan)